Larger than a five pence piece, this huge hornet invaded a family home and took  ten minutes to die after it was sprayed with poison.

The huge insect, which measured 2.5inches, was feared to be a potentially lethal Asian hornet, which are feared to be heading to Britain from France.

It flew into the kitchen of  Rebecca Smith's home in Baldwins Gate, Staffordshire, and even after her partner Michael Elwell doused it in fly spray it continued to tear around the couple's home before it finally died ten minutes later.

