Nature experts also fear that should the hornets make it to Britain they could threaten the already dwindling population of honeybees - which they poison and use to feed their larvae.

Ms Smith, 36, spotted the  winged insect as she went to fetch her stepchildren ice lollies from the freezer on Monday, before calling Mr Elwell, 46, to the rescue.

'I went into the kitchen to fetch two ice lollies for the children and saw it on the window,' she said.

